1
00:00:01,309 --> 00:00:06,309
STRIDER. Tells autonomous Marines what they are rolling onto.

2
00:00:06,311 --> 00:00:11,311
Force Design 2030 puts Marines in places maps do not reach.

3
00:00:11,318 --> 00:00:16,318
LOGCOM fields the autonomous tow tractor at MDMC Albany today, ALPV tomorrow.

4
00:00:16,329 --> 00:00:21,329
Forward rover snaps a frame. GOOSE off-road imagery, never leaves the wire.

5
00:00:18,853 --> 00:00:23,853
Fifty gigabytes of labelled terrain, on-prem.

6
00:00:21,354 --> 00:00:27,354
Kamiwaza-deployed vision call: terrain frame becomes structured JSON.

7
00:00:27,398 --> 00:00:33,398
Soft sand. Very-soft firmness. No water crossing.

8
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:39,400
Reasoner cross-references fording depth and ground clearance per vehicle.

9
00:00:39,403 --> 00:00:45,403
Green, amber, red. Binding constraint named in plain English.

10
00:00:45,405 --> 00:00:51,405
ALPV caution. JLTV caution. ATT-EV NO-GO -- 6.5 inch clearance bogs in soft sand.

11
00:00:51,430 --> 00:00:55,430
Convoy commander has the answer in four seconds.

12
00:00:55,433 --> 00:01:00,433
Audit trail: full JSON every call. Operator can replay any decision.

13
00:01:00,512 --> 00:01:05,512
Set KAMIWAZA_BASE_URL. Same code hits on-prem vLLM. 100% data containment.

14
00:01:05,517 --> 00:01:10,517
IL5 / IL6 ready. STIG-hardened. Inference Mesh handles the routing.

15
00:01:10,519 --> 00:01:15,519
Built on the Kamiwaza Stack. Deploy in hours, not months.
